.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-7-2::.
6 different games are played: canasta, chess, poker, go, monopoly, billiard
The people use 6 different means of transport: trike, helicopter, subway, car, train, van
 1. the person playing canasta is somewhere to the right of the person playing chess##5
 2. the person driving the van is on the left or right of the person playing poker##3
 3. the person driving the train is on the left or right of the person playing monopoly##3
 4. the person playing poker is on the left or right of the person driving the car##3
 5. the person playing billiard is on the left of the person driving the train##1
 6. the person playing monopoly is on the left or right of the person playing poker##3
 7. the person playing monopoly is somewhere to the left of the person playing poker##5
 8. the person playing canasta is on the far left or far right##3
 9. the person playing monopoly is not the person driving the train##6
10. the person driving the trike is somewhere between the person driving the van and the person driving the car##7
11. the person driving the subway is somewhere to the left of the person playing monopoly##5
12. the person playing billiard is on the right of the person driving the helicopter##1
13. the person driving the van is on the left or right of the person driving the trike##3
14. the person driving the van is in an even position##4
15. the person playing go is somewhere to the left of the person driving the car##5
16. the person driving the van is on the right of the person driving the trike##1
17. the person playing go is somewhere between the person driving the helicopter and the person playing monopoly##7

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |      2      |    3    |     4      |     5      |    6     |
| Game   | chess | billiard | go | monopoly     | poker      | canasta |
| Transport           | helicopter         | subway        | train   | car | trike | van    |

